-Start PS-02A — Games Contract and Backend.
-
-Read and follow these files before modifying anything:
-
-- AGENTS.md
-- docs/PRODUCT_RULES.md
-- docs/CURRENT_PHASE.md
-- docs/DECISION_LOG.md
-- docs/MIGRATIONS.md
-
-The active baseline is the completed PS-01 repository state.
-
-Before implementation:
-
-1. Run:
-
-git rev-parse HEAD
-
-Save the result as START_HEAD.
-
-2. Inspect the existing:
-
-- Games schema and enums
-- Games database relations
-- Games API routes and services
-- Accounts relation to Games
-- Orders and Order Items relation to Games
-- OpenAPI Games paths and schemas
-- generated Zod/API client outputs
-- existing migration files and Drizzle configuration
-- existing Games tests
-
-Do not produce a separate long analysis report. Use the inspection to make minimal and safe implementation changes.
-
-## Objective
-
-Implement the approved Games data contract and database-backed Backend.
-
-Do not implement or modify the Games frontend in this phase.
-
-## Canonical Games contract
-
-Platforms must be exactly:
-
-- PS5_ONLY
-- PS4_ONLY
-- PS4_AND_PS5
-
-Statuses must be exactly:
-
-- ACTIVE
-- INACTIVE
-
-The Game model must support:
-
-- UUID primary key
-- title
-- normalized title
-- platform
-- status
-- existing image field if already supported
-- created timestamp
-- updated timestamp
-
-Do not redesign image storage or upload behavior.
-
-## Title normalization
-
-Implement one reusable server-side title-normalization function.
-
-It must:
-
-- trim surrounding whitespace
-- collapse repeated internal whitespace to one space
-- use a consistent case-insensitive representation for duplicate detection
-
-These values must conflict:
-
-- `FC 26`
-- ` fc 26 `
-- `FC   26`
-
-These values must remain distinct:
-
-- `FC 26`
-- `FC 26 Ultimate Edition`
-
-Store the normalized value in the database.
-
-Add a database-level unique index or constraint for the normalized title.
-
-Do not rely only on frontend or route validation.
-
-Map duplicate-title conflicts to a controlled HTTP 409 response without exposing raw PostgreSQL errors.
-
-## Platform protection
-
-A Game platform may be changed only when no Account history exists for that Game.
-
-Once at least one Account references the Game:
-
-- title may still be edited
-- status may still be edited
-- platform changes must return HTTP 409
-
-Use the existing Account relation. Do not redesign Accounts.
-
-## Status behavior
-
-Support:
-
-- ACTIVE
-- INACTIVE
-
-Inactive Games remain stored and retrievable through management API operations.
-
-Do not implement Account or Assignment blocking in this phase. That enforcement belongs to later phases.
-
-## Hard deletion
-
-Hard deletion is allowed only when the Game has no related history.
-
-At minimum:
-
-- if any Account references the Game, deletion must return HTTP 409
-- no Account, Capacity, Order, or historical record may be cascade-deleted
-
-Inspect whether the current schema has a reliable direct or indirect Order-to-Game relation.
-
-If a safe existing relation exists, also block deletion when Order history exists.
-
-If no reliable Order-to-Game relation exists:
-
-- do not invent or redesign the Orders schema
-- implement the Account-history protection
-- report Order-history deletion protection as explicitly deferred to the Orders domain phase
-
-Do not claim that Order-history protection is implemented unless supported by the actual schema and tests.
-
-## Migration requirements
-
-Do not edit, squash, or replace the initial migration.
-
-Create a new versioned Drizzle migration for PS-02A.
-
-Do not use:
-
-- drizzle-kit push
-- drizzle-kit push --force
-- direct schema mutation against the shared Replit database
-
-Do not apply the migration to the current shared database.
-
-Verify against a clean disposable PostgreSQL database by applying:
-
-1. all existing migrations in order
-2. the new PS-02A migration
-
-Report the exact migration result.
-
-## Games API
-
-Use the existing route conventions where reasonable.
-
-Implement or correct database-backed operations for:
-
-- list Games
-- get one Game
-- create Game
-- update Game
-- change Game status
-- hard delete Game
-
-Avoid unnecessary duplicate endpoints when the existing update endpoint can safely manage title, platform, and status.
-
-Required HTTP behavior:
-
-- invalid UUID → 400
-- invalid request body → 400
-- missing Game → 404
-- normalized duplicate title → 409
-- platform change after Account history → 409
-- prohibited hard deletion → 409
-- unexpected failure → controlled 500
-
-Use the PS-01:
-
-- centralized error handler
-- UUID validation utility
-- controlled request parsing
-
-Do not expose database errors, stack traces, SQL, or sensitive values.
-
-Keep validation and normalization logic reusable rather than duplicating it across routes.
-
-Use transactions when an operation contains multiple dependent database actions.
-
-## OpenAPI and generated outputs
-
-Update OpenAPI only for the Games backend contract implemented in this phase.
-
-Regenerate the project’s existing:
-
-- Zod schemas
-- API client
-- related generated outputs
-
-Do not manually modify generated files when generation is available.
-
-Do not connect the frontend Games page to the API yet.
-
-## Required focused tests
-
-Add or update tests for at least:
-
-1. title normalization
-2. duplicate normalized-title rejection
-3. successful Game creation
-4. invalid UUID returning 400
-5. missing Game returning 404
-6. platform change allowed without Account history
-7. platform change blocked with Account history
-8. ACTIVE to INACTIVE status change
-9. hard deletion allowed without history
-10. hard deletion blocked with Account history
-11. hard deletion blocked with Order history only if the current schema safely supports this relation
-12. duplicate conflict does not expose a raw database error
-
-Tests must use isolated test data or a disposable database.
-
-Do not modify the shared Replit database for tests.
-
-## Prohibited changes
-
-Do not modify:
-
-- Games frontend page
-- Games dialogs or animations
-- frontend runtime mock flow
-- Accounts business implementation
-- Capacity templates
-- Orders business implementation
-- Store Mapping
-- Assignment
-- Connector
-- Authentication
-- Staff
-- RBAC
-- Dashboard
-- unrelated UI
-- unrelated schemas or routes
